South Korea’s Overseas Direct Investment Declines by 56.1%

-- B y   W i l l i a m   S i m
-- 
2011-02-23T03:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-23/south-korea-s-overseas-direct-investment-declines-by-56-1-.html
  South Korea ’s overseas direct
investment declined by 56.1 percent in the fourth quarter of
2010 from a year earlier as companies invested in fewer projects.  Investment abroad decreased to $7.23 billion over the three
months through December from $16.47 billion in the same period a
year earlier, the  Ministry of Strategy and Finance  said in an e-
mailed statement today.  Overseas direct investment totaled $32.53 billion in 2010,
up 8.5 percent from the $29.98 billion made in 2009.  To contact the reporter on this story:
William Sim in Seoul at 
